Title: Bias, variance and prediction error for classification rules  
Author: Robert Tibshirani 
Keyword: classification, prediction error, bias, variance, bootstrap  
Note: c flUniversity of Toronto  
Date: November 6, 1996  
Address: Toronto, Canada  
Affiliation: Department of Preventive Medicine and Biostatistics and Department of Statistics University of Toronto  
Abstract: We study the notions of bias and variance for classification rules. Following Efron (1978) we develop a decomposition of prediction error into its natural components. Then we derive bootstrap estimates of these components and illustrate how they can be used to describe the error behaviour of a classifier in practice. In the process we also obtain a bootstrap estimate of the error of a "bagged" classifier. 
